Question: Android record exists() in database?: :I am looking to the fastest and the correct way to check if a record exists in the database:public boolean Exists(String _id) {    Cursor c=db.query(TABLENAME(), new String[] {"1"}, "_ID="+_id, null, null, null, null);    if (!c.equals(null))        return c.moveToFirst();    return false;}Do you see any problem with it?
Please using this api: SQLiteDatabase.query.
Answer:
<<<api>>>: SQLiteDatabase.query
<<<code>>>: public boolean Exists(String _id) {
    Cursor c=db.query(TABLENAME(), new String[] {"1"}, "_ID="+_id, null, null, null, null);
    if (!c.equals(null))
        return c.moveToFirst();
    return false;
}
<<<explanation>>>: The problem with this code is that it is not checking if the cursor is null. If the cursor is null, the code will throw a NullPointerException.
To fix this, you should check if the cursor is null before calling moveToFirst(). You can do this by adding an if statement to check if the cursor is null before calling moveToFirst().
Here is the fixed code:
public boolean Exists(String _id) {
    Cursor c=db.query(TABLENAME(), new String[] {"1"}, "_ID="+_id, null, null, null, null);
    if (c != null) {
        if (c.moveToFirst()) {
            return true;
        }
    }
    return false;
}

This code will check if the cursor is null before calling moveToFirst(). If the cursor is null, the code will return false. If the cursor is not null, the code will check if moveToFirst() returns true. If it does, the code will return true. If it does not, the code will return false.
Please note that this code is not the most efficient way to check if a record exists in the database. It is a simple way to check if a record exists in the database.
